1.title: Crispy Curly Fries
1.plot: Darrell makes his first visit to Dr. Chase Neal to discuss his issues with his brother, Daryl. Daryl's food craving gets his brother, Darrell, in a hot mess.

2.title: The Bossman's Wife
2.plot: Darrell and Dr. Chase Neal discuss Daryl's most recent trip to the supermarket, and his encounter with the bossman's wife.

3.title: Dirty Laundry
3.plot: Darrell and Dr. Chase Neal discuss the brother's recent visit to the laundry mat.

4.title: The Workplace Blues
4.plot: Darrell discusses his "take your brother to work day" experience with Dr. Chase Neal.

5.title: S'mores Galore
5.plot: Darrell and Dr. Chase Neal talk about the brother's recent camping trip gone wrong.

6.title: All We Need Is Love
6.plot: Darrell and Dr. Chase Neal talk over Daryl's introduction to a new female companion, Darla.

7.title: Car-ni-val
7.plot: Darrell and Dr. Chase Neal discuss Daryl's second date with Darla to the town carnival.

8.title: A Lesson Learned
8.plot: Darrell and Dr. Chase Neal reflect on Daryl's behavior with Darla, and how he learns a lesson that was long overdue.

imdb.plot outline: Meet Darrell and Daryl. Two brothers that share the same bloodline, but that's just about where the similarities end. Darrell is a respectful member of society who adheres to social norms. His brother, Daryl, is the black sheep of the family who finds himself in precarious situations through his daily encounters. These situations not only effect Daryl, but often find his brother taking on the brunt of the responsibility. After a lifelong struggle, Darrell begins his journey of venting and help seeking with the guidance of his therapist, Dr. Chase Neal. It is through this relationship that we hear the many tales of adventures, and come to realize that through it all, Darrell just wants the best for his brother.
